commentTextItems.html: beaten outside off stump, a loud appeal from Mahmood and Nixon but it's immaterial, the game is over and England will meet Australia in the best-of-three final

commentPostTextItems.html: Well, written off a week ago, England have come up on the rails to take second place thanks to a super allround performance from Paul Collingwood.  And so we all head to the MCG on Friday as this series nears a close. Bob Dylan has been on his Never-Ending Tour since 1994. It seems as if the CB Series kicked off around the same time.
Join us at 2.15pm (0315GMT) on Friday for more fun frolics and positively no Mexican waves.

dismissalText.commentary: Ross Taylor run out (Vaughan/Flintoff) 25 (27b 1x4 0x6 55m) SR: 92.59

dismissalComment.html: England have got the wicket! And it's a run-out from Flintoff's first ball of the new spell! Fleming defended into the covers and set off for the run, Taylor hesitated, Fleming stopped dead, retreated, Taylor kept on coming, and Flintoff fielded the ball and hurtled down to the non-striker's end! Big breakthrough
